    <text type="letter">  
        <body> 
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03757.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>THE PHILADELPHIA TIMES</name>
                    <date><handShift rend="manuscript"/><hi rend="underline">Wednesday,</hi></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I see that Thorne,<ptr target="loc.03757_n1"/> (who is a literary "mountebank" and
                who has a quarterly Review called the <hi rend="underline">Globe</hi> takes a shy at
                you in his April No.&#8212;It is only a line or two and amounts to nothing!&#8212;</p>
            <p>Stoddart<ptr target="loc.04674_n1"/> manager of <hi rend="underline">Lippincotts</hi><ptr target="loc.07874_n5"/> 
                still treasures up the idea of having you to go to Gloucester to a Symposium: with
                the idea to have it written up for July Lippincott<ptr target="loc.03757_n4"/> as one of the "Round Robin"
                    Series&#8212;<hi rend="underline">It is</hi> a good <hi rend="underline"
                    >idea</hi> and you can say somethings which will be embalmed for futurity. Don't
                you think y<gap reason="cut-away" quantity="12" unit="chars"/> in the early part of
                    <gap reason="cut-away" quantity="6" unit="chars"/> Ju<gap reason="cut-away"
                        quantity="4" unit="chars"/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                <signed>James.</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Couldn't you give me something of interest to the Time for Satur<gap
                    reason="cut-away" quantity="5" unit="chars"/><ptr target="loc.03757_n3"/></p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03757.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ww" place="right">Scovel</note>
        </body>
